# Day 13 – Excel Chart (Bar Chart)

## What I Learned
- Learned how to create charts in Excel with a focus on **Bar Chart**.
- Learned how to create charts using Excel recommendations and manual selection.
- Learned how to customize chart styles, colors, layouts, and models.
- Learned how to add or remove data from an existing chart.
- Learned how to add chart elements and use a secondary axis for better visualization.

## Functions / Features
- **Create Chart**
  - Block/select the data to be visualized.
  - Insert chart manually or use Excel chart recommendations.
- **Chart Styling**
  - Change colors, chart style, layout, and model.
- **Edit Chart Data**
  - Chart Design → Select Data
  - Add new data by selecting the updated data range.
  - Remove data by unchecking or removing unwanted data series.
- **Chart Elements**
  - Chart Design → Add Chart Element
  - Add titles, axis labels, data labels, legend, and gridlines.
- **Secondary Axis**
  - Used when data values have large gaps or differences.
  - Chart Design → Change Chart Type → Combo
  - Enable secondary axis for selected data.

## Practice
- Created a bar chart from selected data.
- Customized chart appearance using styles and layout options.
- Added new data to an existing chart.
- Removed unnecessary data from the chart.
- Applied secondary axis to improve data readability.

## Key Takeaways
- Data must be selected first before creating a chart.
- Chart Design tools allow full customization without recreating the chart.
- Secondary axis is useful when data ranges differ significantly.
- Proper styling and elements make charts clearer and more informative.
